sub_questions: Which rows have 'Accident' in the Time/Retired column?
Which rows have Grid equal to 27?
What are the Laps values for rows meeting all three criteria?
What is the mean of the Laps values after filtering?

format_notes: Laps column is stored as object type but represents numeric counts
Grid column is stored as object type but represents numeric positions
Time/Retired column contains mixed values: time differences (e.g., '+46:22.971') or status strings (e.g., 'Accident')

constraints: Laps must be convertible to numeric for averaging
Grid must be convertible to numeric for comparison with 27
Time/Retired must be checked for substring 'Accident' case-insensitively
derived_filters: Filter where Time/Retired status is 'Accident' (not a time value)
Filter where Grid value equals 27 after numeric conversion
output_format_requirements: Return a single numeric value representing the average
Handle case where no records match the criteria (return null or 0)
Round to appropriate precision for lap counts
